data.content:
Here are the three breaking changes and their fixes:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now takes a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your entire expression-tree construction is no longer needed. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

The new overload accepts `Func<...>` instead of `Expression<Func<...>>`, so hand-built expression trees won't compile anymore — but you no longer need them.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

**Same-level collision:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one column silently. EF 10 appends a number (e.g. `Street1`). To keep old names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress,
        p => p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
});
```

**Nested complex types:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to column `BillingAddress_City`. EF 10 uses the full path: `Payment_BillingAddress_City`. To keep the old name:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

⚠️ If you have existing migrations/data, add a migration after upgrading and review the generated column renames carefully.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method now requires an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (contains redacted SQL for logging). Update your signature:

```csharp
public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
    IRelationalConnection connection,
    DbCommand command,
    DbContext context,
    Guid commandId,
    Guid connectionId,
    DateTimeOffset startTime,
    string logCommandText)   // ← new parameter
{
    // Use logCommandText for logging (constants may be redacted)
    // Use command.CommandText for the actual executed SQL
}
```

Update all methods on the interface similarly (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.).
